description:
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity has risen for a fully qualified Band 7 Highly Specialised Clinical Physiologist (Neurophysiology) with suitable experience to join our Neurophysiological Team within Physiological Measurements at Diana Princess of Wales Hospital, Grimsby.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is suitable for an experienced Neurophysiologist is able to work in a busy department undertaking various Neurophysiological diagnostic tests which will include EEG, Physiologist Lead Nerve Conduction studies Clinic and all modalities of Evoked Potentials and assist Consultant Clinical Neurophysiologist with Special Peripheral Neurophysiological studies and EMG.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We provide a range of highly specialised Diagnostic Neurophysiological studies across the Trust within the department and portables on the wards, for adults and children of all ages as out-patients as well as an active in-patient service which includes intensive care units.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In house training will be given to the post-holder where necessary. CPD and role expansion will be actively encouraged.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kamalakannan Jothi, Head of Neurophysiology&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;kamalakannan.jothi@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;03033 304203&lt;/p&gt;
